verbose_text: Laboratory studies revealed abnormal liver function, including an elevated serum total bilirubin (T-Bil) level of 2.06 mg/dL (upper limit of normal [ULN] : 1.2 mg/dL), direct bilirubin level of 0.55 mg/dL (ULN : 0.25 mg/dL), an elevated liver enzymes SGOT level of 45 IU/L (ULN : 31 IU/L), ALK phosphatase level of 588 (ULN : 306 U/L) with hypoalbuminemia (Serum Albumin-3.3 g/dL; lower limit of normal [LLN] : 3.5 g/dL).
